// X-macro source-of-truth for primitive types.
//
// Each row contributes to several expansions:
//   1. The IpReservedIndex enum (IP_INDEX_BOOL_TYPE, IP_INDEX_U8_TYPE, …)
//      — stable compile-time constants used as the IpIndex.v for each
//      reserved slot.
//   2. The pool's static_keys init in ip_init() — the row's enum
//      position IS its resulting IpIndex.
//   3. ip_key()'s reverse lookup — the tag stored at each reserved
//      index needs to map back to the right IpKey variant.
//   4. Public macros like IP_BOOL_TYPE that callers compare against.
//
// Adding a new primitive: append a row here, recompile. Single source
// of truth eliminates the three-way drift risk Zig's design has between
// Index/static_keys/Air.Inst.Ref.
//
// Columns:
//   X(LOWERCASE_NAME, UPPERCASE_NAME, SIZE_BYTES, ALIGN_BYTES)
//
// LOWERCASE — symbol stem (lowercase identifier).
// UPPERCASE — used inside IP_INDEX_* / IP_*_TYPE / IP_TAG_TYPE_* enum
//   and macro values.
// SIZE / ALIGN — informational; layout queries live elsewhere. 0/1 for
//   zero-sized abstract types (void, type, noreturn, etc.).
//
// Order is part of the ABI: bumping or reordering changes every
// reserved IpIndex's numeric value. Callers comparing against
// IP_BOOL_TYPE etc. don't care, but anything that serializes the
// pool (cross-session caching, future) does.
//
// Only TRUE primitives belong here — types that have no parameters and
// no payload. Compound types (pointers, slices, optionals, arrays, fn,
// struct, enum) live in IpTag with their own storage. const-ness is a
// property of pointer/slice tags, not of bare value types. Reserved
// values (bool true, void, …) live in the IpReservedIndex enum in
// intern_pool.h alongside reserved compound IpIndexes.
//
// No header guard / no macro wrapper — this file is a list of X(...)
// invocations, intended to be #include'd in a context where X has just
// been defined (and is #undef'd after). Standard X-macro pattern.

X(bool,           BOOL,           1, 1)
X(u8,             U8,             1, 1)
X(i8,             I8,             1, 1)
X(u16,            U16,            2, 2)
X(i16,            I16,            2, 2)
X(u32,            U32,            4, 4)
X(i32,            I32,            4, 4)
X(u64,            U64,            8, 8)
X(i64,            I64,            8, 8)
X(f32,            F32,            4, 4)
X(f64,            F64,            8, 8)
X(usize,          USIZE,          TARGET_PTR_SIZE, TARGET_PTR_ALIGN)
X(isize,          ISIZE,          TARGET_PTR_SIZE, TARGET_PTR_ALIGN)
X(void,           VOID,           0, 1)
X(type,           TYPE,           0, 1)
X(anytype,        ANYTYPE,        0, 1)
X(comptime_int,   COMPTIME_INT,   0, 1)
X(comptime_float, COMPTIME_FLOAT, 0, 1)
X(nil,            NIL,            0, 1)
X(error,          ERROR,          0, 1)
X(noreturn,       NORETURN,       0, 1)
